&lt;details class="print:hidden xl:hidden" &gt;
&lt;summary&gt;Table of Contents&lt;/summary&gt;
&lt;div class="text-sm"&gt;
&lt;nav id="TableOfContents"&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#linux"&gt;&lt;span class="section-num"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt; Linux&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#gentoo"&gt;&lt;span class="section-num"&gt;1.1&lt;/span&gt; Gentoo&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#networkmanager"&gt;&lt;span class="section-num"&gt;1.1.1&lt;/span&gt; NetworkManager&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#strongswan-interactions"&gt;&lt;span class="section-num"&gt;1.1.2&lt;/span&gt; Strongswan interactions&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/nav&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/details&gt;
&lt;h2 id="linux"&gt;&lt;span class="section-num"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt; Linux&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="gentoo"&gt;&lt;span class="section-num"&gt;1.1&lt;/span&gt; Gentoo&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h4 id="networkmanager"&gt;&lt;span class="section-num"&gt;1.1.1&lt;/span&gt; NetworkManager&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Open the NetworkManager UI, then:
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Go to Network &amp;gt; VPN. Click &lt;em&gt;+&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Select &lt;em&gt;Layer 2 Tunneling Protocol (L2TP)&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You can choose a name for the VPN.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enter Your VPN Server IP for the Gateway.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enter Your VPN Username for the User name.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Right-click the &lt;em&gt;?&lt;/em&gt; in the Password field, select Store the password only for this user.
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You might want to use &lt;em&gt;Store password for all users&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enter Your VPN Password for the Password.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leave the NT Domain field blank.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Click the &lt;em&gt;IPsec Settings&amp;hellip;&lt;/em&gt; button.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Check the Enable IPsec tunnel to L2TP host checkbox.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leave the Gateway ID field blank.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enter Your VPN IPsec PSK for the Pre-shared key.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Then click &lt;em&gt;Add&lt;/em&gt; to save the VPN connection information.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4 id="strongswan-interactions"&gt;&lt;span class="section-num"&gt;1.1.2&lt;/span&gt; Strongswan interactions&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;By default, strongswan is built with capabilities support and the ability to run as an unprivileged user.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;However, capabilities are not configured in NetworkManager.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;As a result, the connection is not established.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You can solve the problem as follows:
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;either install strongswan without capabilities support and the ability to run as an unprivileged user:
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-shell" data-lang="shell"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="nv"&gt;USE&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="s2"&gt;&amp;#34;-caps -non-root&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; emerge strongswan
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;either build NetworkManager with capabilities support (see
).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>Package manager for Windows. Chocolatey</title><link>https://yamadharma.github.io/en/post/2021/01/18/package-manager-windows-chocolatey/</link><pubDate>Mon, 18 Jan 2021 11:23:00 +0300</pubDate><guid>https://yamadharma.github.io/en/post/2021/01/18/package-manager-windows-chocolatey/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;The most popular package manager for Windows is &lt;em&gt;Chocolatey&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
